00:10:11.885 --> 00:10:13.885
It's been a bad day trying to get my phone fixed.

182
00:10:13.885 --> 00:10:16.885
Oh, what's wrong with your phone?

183
00:10:19.885 --> 00:10:21.885
Hi Gail, how are you today?

184
00:10:21.885 --> 00:10:22.885
Not great.

185
00:10:22.885 --> 00:10:24.885
It's been a bad day trying to get my phone fixed.

186
00:10:24.885 --> 00:10:29.045
fixed. Oh, sorry to hear that. Let's see what we can do to turn that around.

187
00:10:30.805 --> 00:10:35.045
Just by acknowledging their feelings and demonstrate your desire to help them,

188
00:10:35.445 --> 00:10:40.005
you've started to build a relationship with the user. Of course, you have to keep up the good

189
00:10:40.005 --> 00:10:44.005
work throughout the interaction, but laying the groundwork is an important first step.

190
00:10:44.565 --> 00:10:48.645
And remember that while you might have a hundred issues in the ticket queue that need

191
00:10:48.645 --> 00:10:54.565
your attention, this is the only one that matters to the user. So show them it's your priority too.

